      "writtenOn": "2026-05-06T16:08:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Shouldn\u0027t it be Off only if all chassis are off? If we are powering off the system, it is not completely off until all the individual chassis having powered off.\n\nAlso, for both power on and power off, note that some chassis may be excluded. They might be missing, in hardware isolation, not able to communicate, etc. So the aggregation should be over the chassis that were selected for power on/power off I think? For example, if a chassis is missing, it is \"Off\", but that should not stop the aggregated power changing to \"On\" when all the present chassis finish powering on.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 14,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 14,
        "endChar": 57
      },
      "revId": "5f3c0079fe7d6b6d5b99cd254272b3706263cc0c",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
