      "writtenOn": "2026-05-13T20:07:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, good point, this commit was just On/Off, and then later in https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/phosphor-state-manager/+/88977 I support the transitioning concepts and also correct what you noted here, that if any Chassis is On then the reported state will be On.\n\n\nLater commits also address the presence concept (so we\u0027ll only power on/off chassis that are present). Commits not yet up yet will move to the Available concept so chassis which are unavailable for a variety of reasons will also not be included in what is logically on/off.\n\nAs noted by Matt in previous commits I probably took the \"small commit\" concept a bit too far here but I\u0027d prefer to just keep things as-is for now given the end result of the patch series will address your comment here.",
